      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 31
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Presenting a pristine 1997 Porsche 911 Carrera (993), the final evolution of the air-cooled flat-six. This example features the 3.6L M64 engine with the VarioRam induction system, optimizing mid-range torque and peak volumetric efficiency. Power is managed via a G50 six-speed manual transaxle, renowned for its precise shift gates and robust synchros. The chassis retains its original 'Weissach' multi-link rear suspension geometry, ensuring neutral handling and superior lateral grip. Every seal remains tight, with zero evidence of oil weepage from the crankcase or valve covers. The paint depth is consistent across all factory panels, and the interior demonstrates zero UV degradation on the leather or dash. This is a mechanically transparent, investment-grade vehicle for the serious air-cooled aficionado.",
      "price": 49500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
